<html><head><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8" /><meta http-equiv="Content-Style-Type" content="text/css" /><meta name="generator" content="Aspose.Words for .NET 13.4.0.0" /><title>SBS Submission to the Joint Committee on Human Rights</title></head><body><div><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Written evidence submitted by Southall Black Sisters (LAI 0080)</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; text-decoration:underline">Summary</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Southall Black Sisters has serious concerns </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">about the government’s response to its consultation:</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic"> Transforming Legal Aid</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">'</span><a name="_ftnref1"></a><a href="#_ftn1">[1]</a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">. Notwithstanding the announced concessions, the proposals will</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">prevent </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">larger numbers of poor </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">and extremely vulnerable groups from accessing justice and protection. The measures </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">strike at the heart of the equality principle and the rule of law and are irreconcilable with the government’s commitment t</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">o international human rights.</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="2" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The retention of the residence test will have far reaching consequences for those who do not reside in</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> the UK but who need to hold the British State to account for unlawful actions </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">committed by </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">State</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> and non-State actors</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">. The measure will contribute to a culture of impunity for abuses of power in which the State is dir</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ectly and indirectly implicated.</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="3" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">list of exempted categories in respect of the residence test set out in Schedule I of LASPO covers very specific and narrow legal matters</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">. It will</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">exclude</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">exempted and other </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">vulnerable </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">categories such as women and </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">children </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">subject to domestic violence from</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> accessing </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">legal aid </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">for inter-related</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> matters. F</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">or example</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">, migrant women subject to violence will not be able to </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">challenge public bodies by way of judicial review </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">in circumstances </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">where there is failure to provide accommodation and </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">welfare </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">support </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">in acc</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ordance with their legal obligations</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">. The residence test will lead to fundamental </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">breaches </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">of the human rights of vulnerable </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">women and children </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">who are entitled to equal protection under </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">the Government’s own policies and strategies on violence against wome</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">n and under </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">international human rights law and standards</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> including those on discrimination </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">and violence </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">against women</span><a name="_ftnref2"></a><a href="#_ftn2">[2]</a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">.</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="4" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The denial of access to legal aid to foreign nationals who experience abuse, violence or ill-treatment whilst in immigration or prison </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">detention will amount to a license for such violations to continue</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> unchecked</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">. The recent coverage of the sexual abuse of female detainees in immigration detention points to the dangerous, unfair and discrim</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">inatory impact of such measures.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span></li></ol><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="5" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">There is consid</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">erable evidence to show that the exceptional funding regime which is relied upon by the government as a safeguard against violations of human rights is not fit for purpose.</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="6" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The new proposals will exacerbate access to justice since it builds on an already </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">problematic </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">and discriminatory </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">LASPO </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">regime, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">which</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> along with the latest proposals have</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> not been properly evaluated for </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">their</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> e</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">quality and human rights impact.</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; text-decoration:underline">About Southall Black Sisters (SBS)</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="7" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">For the past 30 years, SBS has provided advocacy and support to black and minority women who </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">make up</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> some of the most </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">marginalised </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">and disadvantaged sections of our society and </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">are </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">therefore </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">often very ‘hard to reach’. Many arrive at SBS having experienced</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> violence and abuse and related problems of homelessness, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">mental illness, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">poverty and insecure immigration status. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The bulk of our work is directed at assisting women and children obtain effective protection and assert their fundamental human rights. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Thro</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ugh front line </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">advocacy</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> work, we assist on average 3000 women a year</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> to access </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">housing, welfare support and mental health services and</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> legal advice and representation in family, immigration, criminal</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">, community care</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> and </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">other </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">legal proceedings.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Our work by</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> its very nature addresses issues of multiple or intersectional discrimination, involving the simultaneous experience of race, gender and other forms of </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">inequality</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">.</span><a name="_ftnref3"></a><a href="#_ftn3">[3]</a></li></ol><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; text-decoration:underline">Holding the State to account</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="8" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The government’s intention to proceed with a residence test will exclude </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">British and </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">foreign nationals who have not lived in the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">UK</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> continuously for 12 months prior to making an application for </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">civil </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">legal aid. This will result in serious cases of state ab</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">use </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">of power </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">remaining unchecked. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">C</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ases </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">brought by </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">the families of </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Charles</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> de</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Meneze</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">s</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">, Jimmy </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Mubenga</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">and </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Baha</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Mousa</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> would not have taken place had the residence test been in place.</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="9" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 32pt; padding-left:4pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">SBS is</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> concerned with another dimension of this problem – the exclusion of</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> cases involving abuses of power committed by</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> non-state actors in which the S</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">tate is implicated. For example, we often assist families who live abroad but whose daughters have, upon marriage to British nationals, been killed or have been driven to </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">attempt </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">or </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">commit suicide </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">due to their experiences of</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> domestic violence in the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">UK</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">. These are</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> often cases in which the risks to the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">victims</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> are</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> known or ought to have </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">been </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">known </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">by the State </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">or where there has been complete failure of the State to undertake effecti</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ve investigation into the circumstances surrounding the</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ir</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> death</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">s</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">/serious injuries</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> Often the families of such women turn to </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">SBS in search of answers</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The residence test </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">will</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">exclude </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">such </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">families from access to legal aid despite the legal merit</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">s</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> of the ca</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">se. The following case </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">serves as a powerful </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">illustrat</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ion</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> of the</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> potentially </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">devastating</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> impact of the residence test</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">:</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">Nosheen’s</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold"> case</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">Nosheen</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic"> came to the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">UK</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic"> on a spousal visa in 2006 to join her British national husband </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">and in-laws </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">following an arranged marriage in </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">Pakistan</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">. From the outset of her marriage, she was repeated</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">ly</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic"> abuse</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">d, imprisoned and </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">forced to conceive. She </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">was </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">forbidden from having contact with her family in </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">Pakistan</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:ital