mes New Roman'; font-size:12pt">T</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">he government’s proposal to allow some ‘limited circumstances’ where applicants for civil legal aid on certain matters</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> of law (set out in Schedule 1 to LAPSO) </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">would not</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">be r</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">equired to meet the residence test</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> are in our view, inadequate and will cause irreparable harm</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">; it will take away the final safety net that our users depend on for protection</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">. The exceptions to the re</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">sidence test are set out in Para </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">125</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> of Annexe B</span><a name="_ftnref4"></a><a href="#_ftn4">[4]</a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 28.3pt 0pt 0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 28.3pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">“…t</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">he test will not apply to the following categories of case (which broadly relate to an individual’s liberty, or where the individual is particul