eave to remain under the Domestic Violence Rule in i</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">mmigration law. Many of our cases </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">however, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">involve </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">complex, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">multiple and </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">overlapping </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">issues all of which need to be addressed simultaneously</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> if protection i</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">s</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> to be meaningful</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">O</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">btaining protection orders</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> or regularising immigration status is important but </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">not of itself sufficient for protection. O</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">btaining</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> alternative financial, ho</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">using and other welfare support is also </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">critical to effective </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">long term rehabilitation.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span></li></ol><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-f