nt-size:12pt; font-style:italic"> spent three years in immigration detention during which</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">she was </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">ill treated and </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">denied access to urgent medical treatment. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">She states that </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">immigration officials</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic"> often</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic"> shouted at her and treated her like an </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">‘</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">animal</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">’ causing her to</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic"> suffe</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">r</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic"> a complete mental </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">health breakdown. With the assistance of immigration lawyers, she was</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic"> eventually</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic"> able to leave the detention centre and was granted refugee status for five years. She </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">brought a claim</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">against the UK</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">BA</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic"> for </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">unlawful detention and </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">ill-treatment experienced dur</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">ing detention. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">Her claim was settled in September 201 and she was awarded 42,500 in damages. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">Her </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">detention </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">and ill </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">- </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">treatment has had a </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">permanent impact on her </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">mental </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">health</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">. She is suffering from chronic post - traumatic stress disorder.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="23" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">SBS is</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> concerne</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">d that under the current</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> legal aid</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> proposals, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Sudarshan’s</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> claim </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">partly </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">based on her ill-treatment whilst in detention would be</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> excluded by</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> the residence test</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">. Her case and t</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">he</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> recent</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> exposure</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> o</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">f</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> sexual abuse in </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Yarl’s</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> Wood</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> Immigration Detention Centre</span><a name="_ftnref6"></a><a href="#_ftn6">[6]</a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">is</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">a stark reminder </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">to the government </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">of the need to protect </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">vulnerable </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">individuals in a </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">range </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">of circumstances</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> rather than through arbitrarily identified areas</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> for which t</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">he government has given no </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">satisfactory reason</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">for putting</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> out</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">side the</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">scope</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> of legal</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">.</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; text-decoration:underline">The e</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; text-decoration:underline">xceptional funding </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; text-decoration:underline">regime</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="24" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Our casework experience shows that </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">the ‘exceptional funding scheme’ does not work. Although the government </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">continues to </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">justif</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">y </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">unprecedented cuts to legal aid</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> by claiming that the s</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">cheme will act as a safety net and will </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">protect the right to access justice, the reality is far removed from the rhetoric. </span></li></ol><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="25" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">SBS</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">’</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> casework experience </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">highlighted by case</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">s like that</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> of </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Mawahsi</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">shows that it is extremely difficult </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">if not impossible </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">for applicants to obtain exceptional funding. Ou</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">r views are also echoed by the Public Law Project (PLP) </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">which </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">reports that the process of applying for exceptional funding is extremely onerous and impenetrable</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">, especially for litigants in person</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">T</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">he PLP notes that in the first 3 months of LASPO, the L</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">eg</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">al Aid </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">A</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">gency (LAA)</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> only received 233 applications for exceptional funding</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> and on that basis would </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">have </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">only receive</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">d</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> about</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> 1000 applications in the first year of LASPO</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">. This is</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> far short of the 5000 -7000</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> applications </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">per year </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">anticipated </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">by the Ministry </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">of Justice</span><a name="_ftnref7"></a><a href="#_ftn7">[7]</a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">failure of the L</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">A</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">A to grant exceptional funding </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">compels </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">the PLP </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">to </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">conclude that the exceptional funding </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">scheme </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">is </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">not fit for purpose. </span></li></ol><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; text-decoration:underline">Equality Impact Assessments</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="26" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Finally, in our consultation response to the EIA </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">in relation to </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">Transforming Legal Aid</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">, we concluded that no proper EIA had been conducted</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> in</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> respect of </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">all the main equali</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ty</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> strand</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">s</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> including intersecting equality strands (i.e. where multiple forms of discrimination is experienced simultaneously</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">We argued that given </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">the potentially serious impact of the proposals on many vulnerable groups, the standard of scrutiny in the equality impact assessment by the Ministry of Justice must be high. Our view is that this standard has not been achieved in previous and in the curre</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">nt legal aid proposals. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The proposed residence test in particular will lead to unequal and discriminatory outcomes for all vulnerable groups and will contribute to a set of conditions in which inequality, discrimination and unlawful State actions will beco</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">me legitimised.</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; text-decoration:underline">Recommendations</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; text-decoration:underline"> for the Committee</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="27" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">To scrutinise</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> the latest proposals on legal aid</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">with reference to the UK’s </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">duty </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">to protect </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">all </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">vulnerable adults and children, irrespective of immigration status, under</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> domestic </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">law and policies </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">and international human rights obligations and standards. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The notion of protection should be given its widest meaning, referring not only to the need for immediate protection from danger but also to ensure protection of wider rights. </span></li></ol><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="28" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">To support the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">outcome of a</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> recent</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ly concluded</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">CEDAW</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> Committee </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">inquiry on the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">UK</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">, urging </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">UK</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> government </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">to ensure </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">that women, especially victims of domestic violence, have e</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ffective access to courts and tribunals and to ensure adequate protection of women’s human righ</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ts.</span><a name="_ftnref8"></a><a href="#_ftn8">[8]</a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span></li></ol><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="29" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">To scrutinise the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Government’s p</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">urported EIAs</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> on the legal aid</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">proposals and </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">to highlight the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">manifest </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">inadequacy of the</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">se assessments and of the ‘exceptional fund</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ing regime’ which does not mitigate or minimise the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">highly </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">discriminatory and dispropo</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">rtionate impact of the proposals.</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">26 September 2013</span></p><div style="width:auto; height:auto; float:left;"><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">1</span></p></div><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div><hr style="width:33%; height:1px; text-align:left" /><p style="font-size:10pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn1"></a><a href="#_ftnref1">[1]</a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:10pt"> SBS’</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:10pt"> R</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:10pt">esponse (4 June 2013) to ‘Transforming Legal Aid’:  Consultation Paper, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:10pt">Ministry of Justice available at SBS.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn2"></a><a href="#_ftnref2">[2]</a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:10pt"> See for example the Convention on the Elimination of all Forms of Discrimination against Women, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:10pt">t</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:10p